Prerequisites

1. Install mise
   curl https://mise.run | sh
2. Toolchain + deps
   mise install
   uv sync
3. Chromium + unzip (Ubuntu)
   sudo add-apt-repository ppa:xtradeb/apps -y
   sudo apt update
   sudo apt install -y chromium unzip
4. SeleniumBase driver bundle (Chrome 146 in this repo)
   uv run sbase get uc_driver 146

Environment

1. Create env file
   cp .env.example .env
2. Set at least:
   GEONODE_USER=<value>
   GEONODE_PASS=<value>
   GEONODE_TYPE=residential|datacenter|mix
   GEONODE_PORT=10000-10900 (sticky HTTP range)
   GEONODE_COUNTRY=<country_code_or_empty>
   GEONODE_LIFETIME=3..1440 (minutes)
3. Optional (only if Chromium is not auto-detected):
   CHROME_BINARY=/absolute/path/to/chrome

Run

Default behavior:
- Success rows are appended to `out.csv`.
- Failed rows are appended to `out.errors.csv` with attempt, session, proxy, and timestamp.
- If `out.csv` already has RUCs, they are skipped automatically.
- Sticky sessions are always used (one concurrent sticky session per worker).

uv run robot \
  --input samples.csv \
  --output out.csv \
  --workers 3 \
  --page-size 100 \
  --session-budget 4 \
  --wait-min-s 6 \
  --wait-max-s 10 \
  --same-session-retries 1 \
  --ban-cooldown-s 180 \
  --env-file .env
